songs.title: Sell My Soul*
songs.lyrics:
Lyrics from Snippets

[Verse: Lil Baby]
[...] gangster, he just actin'
Ain't got no card, don't do no fraud
Seem like all of my bitches plastic
None you niggas don't want smoke
They see you runnin' up the fastest
Kill fire when I'm cold
They can never catch me lackin'
I don't know if they think I'm sweet 'cause I'm rappin'
But fuck 'em, we get active
Rappin', make sure they can't smell it
Drive too far, a mile a minute
Tryna steal swag, I see it, I smell it
Used to get mad, probably beat up my city
Now I sell bags every day in my city
Ain't doin' no playin', when they come, be ready
I got murder on my mind like that lil' nigga Melly
Big boy rocks probably same size as Millie
Long as I live, I'ma get this cheddar
Ever since the bitch left, ain't doin' no better
Which car I'ma drive? It depend on the weather
Rolls Royce truck pull up like, "Hello"
Pretty, tall, light skin, shit like Jello
If the bitch act bougie, I'ma take her to the ghetto
If I ain't smokin' Runtz, then it's probably Limoncello
You got lil' boys, but you not on my level
Sell P's every day in the hood on my schedule
Young nigga give a whole ho good like stellar
Tell her don't shake like that, that's jealous
Made a whole M, I don't rock with that, let go
I'm a real boss in my hood, I got say-so
I was havin' choppas 'fore I heard about Dracos
Put me in the casket with a bust down halo, yeah

[Chorus: Lil Baby]
I sell my soul, I–

[Verse: Lil Wayne]
[?] drugs and guns
I feel like, "Where the hell is my grave?"
Heart beat-beatin' at a high rate
World stop spinnin', start to vibrate
It's a cold one, so my house in Miami still came with a fireplace
